# Imports from project root (path aliases)

## Rule

- **MUST** import using **path aliases** rooted at the project directory (`baseUrl` in `tsconfig.json`), not by walking up with `../`.
- **MUST NOT** use parent-segment relative imports in application code: `../`, `../../`, `../../../`, etc.

## Allowed patterns

Configured aliases (see `tsconfig.json` `paths`):

- `app/...`, `components/...`, `hooks/...`, `lib/...`, `modules/...`, `screens/...`, `utils/...`

The `repositories` package resolves via `baseUrl` (barrel at `repositories/index.ts`):

- `import { … } from "repositories"`

Same-directory imports are fine when appropriate:

- `import { … } from "./foo"` (sibling / colocated file only)

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — parent-relative
import { appColors } from "../../lib/theme/appColors";
import { AccountForm } from "../../../components/account/AccountForm";

// ✅ GOOD — root / alias
import { appColors } from "lib/theme/appColors";
import { AccountForm } from "components/account/AccountForm";
import { accountsRepo } from "repositories";
```

## When editing

If you see `../` in an import path, rewrite it to the correct alias. Match existing project imports for consistency.
